pddl.prompt:
Your role is CityPlanner. You are planning a trip involving movement between cities based on direct flight availability. The overall task is to plan a 15-day trip. Focus on modeling the locations (Vienna, Vilnius, Valencia) and the connectivity based on direct flights.
Public information:
{environment->public_information}
Private knowledge:
{agents->CityPlanner->private_information}
Global Goal:
{agents->CityPlanner->goal}
Generate the PDDL domain and problem reflecting city connectivity and possible travel actions. Do not make assumptions about time or duration.
Enclose the pddl domain between <domain></domain> tags, and the pddl problem between <problem></problem> tags.

Your role is TimeScheduler. You are planning the temporal allocation for a 15-day trip. Focus on modeling time steps, required minimum/maximum stays in Vienna (5 days), Vilnius (5 days), and Valencia (7 days), and fixed schedule points (conference in Valencia on Day 9 and Day 15).
Public information:
{environment->public_information}
Private knowledge:
{agents->TimeScheduler->private_information}
Global Goal:
{agents->TimeScheduler->goal}
Generate the PDDL domain and problem reflecting temporal requirements and constraints. Do not worry about city connectivity.
Enclose the pddl domain between <domain></domain> tags, and the pddl problem between <problem></problem> tags.
